    <title>All About Bats</title> </head> <body> <header> <h1>All About Bats</h1> 
    <h2>The fascinating creatures of the night</h2> </header> <main> <section> <h2>Introduction to Bats</h2> 
    <p>Bats are the only mammals capable of sustained flight. They belong to the order Chiroptera, which means "hand-wing."</p> 
    <p>With over 1,400 species, bats play crucial roles in ecosystems, from pollination to pest control.</p> 
    </section> <section> <h2>Types of Bats</h2> 
    <p>There are two main types of bats:</p>
 <ul> <li><strong>Fruit bats</strong> (Megabats): Often larger and feed on fruits and nectar.
    </li> <li><strong>Microbats</strong>: Smaller and use echolocation to hunt insects.
    </li> </ul> </section> <section> <h2>Why Bats are Important</h2> 
    <p>Bats contribute to the environment by:</p> <ul>
 <li>Pollinating plants like bananas and mangoes.</li> <li>Controlling insect populations by eating pests.</li> <li>Spreading seeds for forest growth.</li> 
    </ul> </section> <section> 
